From 9feb3fe403de945e2545e7421505ea1701d55603 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: t <t@t>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 08:01:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] test(contract): ratchet against new Cyrillic in source code
 outside i18n/
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A test that scans all JS/TS source under repo root and flags Cyrillic
characters (Russian display text) appearing OUTSIDE i18n/, comments,
tests and assets.

Architecture: ratchet vs baseline.
- domain/cyrillic-baseline.json — frozen list of 38 legacy files that
  currently contain Russian. They are the to-do for incremental i18n
  migration.
- The test fails when a NEW file (not in baseline) gets Cyrillic added.
- The test fails when a file in baseline is now CLEAN — you must remove
  it from baseline so the ratchet stays tight (otherwise nothing prevents
  re-adding Russian to it later).
- The test logs current debt size for visibility.

Scanner details:
- Excludes /node_modules/, /.git/, /__tests__/, /assets/, /i18n/.
- Excludes *.test.js / *.test.tsx (tests can legitimately need ru text).
- Strips // and /* */ comments BEFORE scanning (line numbers preserved),
  so JSDoc / inline notes referencing Russian words don't trigger.
- Cyrillic detection: /[\u0400-\u04FF]/ (covers all Russian letters
  incl. ё).

Workflow:
  1) Write a feature.
  2) Run tests. If you accidentally typed Russian → red, fix it
     (use tXxx(...) helper from i18n).
  3) When you migrate a legacy file off Russian → red telling you to
     update baseline. Remove the entry, commit.

Baseline composition (38 files): UI screens, modals and a few helpers
that still embed Russian strings — main targets for follow-up i18n PRs.
